in Los Angeles, especially in the 1870s, 1880s,

00:32:50.060 --> 00:32:56.290
was to remove themselves from the Spanish
colonial city. They were trying to make it

00:32:56.290 --> 00:33:00.260
an American city, but not when it came to
the river. When it came to the river, they

00:33:00.260 --> 00:33:08.580
wanted to stay Mexican, because in Mexican,
in the Mexican tradition was the pueblo owns

00:33:08.580 --> 00:33:14.950
the water. So, in the American system, if
your house butts up on the river, that water's

00:33:14.950 --> 00:33:23.650
yours, but not in the Mexican or Spanish system.
So, the city of Los Angeles, somehow, kept

00:33:23.650 --> 00:33:30.090
the river and owned the river. And so, since
water was dear to everybody in Southern California,

00:33:30.090 --> 00:33:35.460
all these cities ended up joining Los Angeles
and that's how Los Angeles got so much bigger.

00:33:35.460 --> 00:33:41.100
Especially like a place like the San Fernando
Valley, where they just needed water desperately,

00:33:41.100 --> 00:33:46.650
so they, and Hollywood, too was annexed by
the city of Los Angeles because of the water.

00:33:46.650 --> 00:33:53.370
So, this is a map. On one side, there's East
Los Angeles, but that's what this is. Again,

00:33:53.370 --> 00:34:00.760
they're selling the property to make money,
